originally marketed as " pringles newfangled potato chips " , pringles are sold in more than 140 countries , and it was the fourth most popular snack brand after lay 's , doritos and cheetos in 2012 , with 2.2 % market share globally , compared to lay 's share of 6.7 % .

guinness records : in 1970 the pringles plant in tennessee produced one of these measuring 23 " x 14 1/2 " -- yum ! yum !

